Visualization: Case 1- Reduce Churn by Targeting High-Risk Consumer Customers 5


Positive Insight:

The Consumer segment has a churn rate of 63%, with 126 churned customers, representing a significant portion of total churn. The GPM for the Consumer segment is 17.7%, which indicates the average profitability per customer. A high percentage of churned customers are classified as high-risk, making them a target for retention efforts to reduce churn effectively.





Negative Insight:

Despite the 17.7% GPM (indicating lower average profit per customer compared to Corporate), retention efforts in this segment are more costly. However, with a 150% ROI, targeting high-risk customers is still a cost-effective way to reduce churn.
Zoom image.png



Case 1 ROI:
Targeting high-risk Consumer customers could save $88,306.53, with an ROI of 150%. This high ROI shows a strong return relative to intervention costs.
